
Package

import java.util.Scanner;



Scanner is used to handle inputs

// Create Scanner object
Scanner myScanner = new Scanner(System.in);


// Reading next inputs
int data = myScanner.nextInt();

// simillarly read double , float 


// Reading string 
String s = myScanner.nextLine();


// Important Notes


1. Reading data of multiple types specially reading string after int / or float 

// use this technique 

int data = Integer.parseint(myScanner.nextLine());
String s = myScanner.nextLine();




2.Reading multiple integer like reading array elements

e.g. 

5
1 2 3 4 5

// use this technique

int n = myScanner.nextInt();

int myArray[] = new int[n];

for(int i=0 ; i<n ;i++)
{
    myArray[i] = myScanner.nextInt();
}


















